          "agH1": "Silver Water - Essence and Effect",
          "ag1P1": "Dr. Harry Margraf, a biochemist and the first researcher of silver, has always claimed: \"Thanks to the results of modern research, silver can be considered a miracle of medicine. The antimicrobial effect of silver acts against many microorganisms: Escherichia coli, Salmonella cholera-suis, Staphylococcus pneumoniae, Staphylococcus epidermidis, Klebsiella pneumoniae, Pseudomonas aeruginosa, Enterococcus faecalis.\"",
          "ag1P2": "Silver preparations have antiviral effects and destroy influenza viruses of strains A1 and B, Coxsackie viruses, and many others. This allows them to be used as therapeutic agents in the treatment of many bacterial infections. Silver water is water saturated with dissolved silver ions. It has antimicrobial and antiseptic properties.",
          "ag1P3": "The water does not contain harmful impurities: dyes, preservatives, oxidizers. Water with silver ions is a natural antibiotic. When silver ions enter the body, they quickly and easily penetrate the membranes of bacteria and stop their vital activities.",
          "ag1P4": "Silver water is an enemy not only of bacteria but also of viruses, which cannot adapt to protect themselves against ions, as is the case with antibiotics and antiviral medications. Colloidal silver water contains electrically charged micro-particles of silver (ranging from 0.01 to 0.001 microns in diameter). Therefore, colloidal silver particles represent a kind of \"generator\" of silver ions.",
          "agUsageH1": "How do people use silver water?",
          "agUsageP1": "People have been using silver water for treatment for over 2000 years. For many years, silver preparations have found wide application in the treatment of humans and animals:<br />• as a natural antimicrobial agent for rinsing the nasal cavity (in respiratory infections).<br />• as a natural antimicrobial agent for gargling (in infections and inflammations).<br />• as a natural antimicrobial agent for gums (in periodontitis, stomatitis).",
          "agBacteriaH1": "How does silver water destroy harmful bacteria?",
          "agBacteriaP1": "The antimicrobial effect of silver does not depend on the type of infection (like antibiotics) but on the cellular structure of the microbe. Any cell without a chemically resistant wall is susceptible to silver attack. The bactericidal and antiviral properties of colloidal silver are much higher than those of previous generations of silver preparations (based on silver salts).",
          "agBacteriaP2": "Bacteria and viruses die. Silver has a significant advantage compared to synthetic antibiotics. At the same time, the spectrum of action of colloidal silver (silver water) extends to 650 species of bacteria (in comparison: the spectrum of action of any antibiotic is 510 species of bacteria) and does not have a harmful effect on beneficial microorganisms and intestinal microflora.",
          "agBacteriaP3": "The beneficial microflora of the internal organs remains unchanged. Therefore, a person who uses it is not at risk of dysbiosis. In other words, silver water will help avoid the situation of 'when we treat one and cripple another.' However, it should be used moderately and in the correct concentration.",
          "agPropertiesH1": "Properties of Silver Water",
          "agPropertiesP1": "The properties of silver water include its ability to heal internal organs. This is due to the complex structure of silver water and the water contained in our body, which rearranges itself to match the structure of silver water.",
          "agPropertiesP2": "Since ancient times, humanity has known that silver has disinfectant properties. Silver items are used not only as decoration but also for water disinfection. Colloidal silver freely penetrates the cell and heals the body:<br />- helps heal hard-to-treat wounds;<br />- restores cells after burns;<br />- is used for rinsing the nose, mouth, throat, and ear canals.",
          "agPropertiesP3": "After the drinking water comes into contact with silver, it acquires completely new qualities. First of all, such water can be stored for a long time because most of the microorganisms present in it die. If you compare silver with copper or gold, it is much more effective at killing microbes. Today, chlorine is widely used to remove microbes from water.",
          "agAdvantagesH1": "Advantages of Silver over Chlorine",
          "agAdvantagesP1": "- Silver is capable of accumulating the energy of the moon, and therefore silver water has miraculous energy properties.<br />- Kills most bacteria and microbes in water, providing a cleaner and safer drinking liquid.<br />- Does not spoil the taste of the water; on the contrary, it preserves its natural and fresh taste.<br />",
          "agAdvantagesP2": "Silver is vital for our body. Without it, the normal functioning of the brain and spinal cord, as well as the work of internal organs that produce various hormones, is impossible. Silver-ionized water stimulates and positively affects the processes in our body, internal organs, and blood."

